description: From the Middle English proponen (“to put forward”), from Latin prōpōnere (“to put forward”), from prō- (“before”) + pōnere (“to put”). Doublet of propose.

verbs.description: propound (third-person singular simple present propounds, present participle propounding, simple past and past participle propounded)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To put forward; to offer for discussion or debate.
examples: Synonyms: put forward, advance, offer, propose
